George, 57, from Sumner emailed me: "just received my new healthcare cost. up 71% ... now they want 909 per month with 6500 deductible"
Katherine from Lawrenceville: "The biggest problem with the ACA is that the promise of being able to keep our current covered... was a lie"
Stephanie, mom of 3 in Danville, says her family's deductible went up $6K. "Obamacare should be repealed and taken off the books," she says.
David in Flora writes: "My wife just got her insurance renewal. Her monthly premium will be $1082 every month!!!!" Says ACA "needs to stop!"
Bradley from Mahomet, another vet, says before ACA he paid $78/mo for his child's coverage...He now pays $167.44/mo for "a much worse plan"
Lisa from Bismark says her "monthly premium has gone from a little over $200 to currently $450" In May she says she'll be forced to pay $678
David in Highland, married w/ 2 teens, went from paying $500/m w/ $1,500 deductible to $990/m w/ $12,600 deductible "for far less coverage"
Jan from Neoga paid $254/m for a plan she liked. Now she pays $858/mo for the same policy. Says "ACA will be the demise of the Middle Class"
Larry, a veteran from Bethany, tells me his wife's insurance went from $610/mo to $1,000/mo. Says "something needs to be done about this."
